sentences.sentence: My copy was dogeared after the first day!
sentences.translation: 我手中的这一本在第一天就被翻旧了！

sentences.sentence: His dogeared book is indicative of his diligent study.
sentences.translation: 被他翻的破烂的书表明他学习很刻苦。

sentences.sentence: The third has a few books or many every one of them dogeared and dilapidated, shaken and loosened by continual use, marked and scribbled in from front to back.
sentences.translation: 第三种人藏书或多或少—因不断使用，每本书都书角卷起，破旧不堪，装订破损，书页松散，全书从扉页至末页都画满了记号，涂满了字句。
